3014:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_tim.c **** /**
3015:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_tim.c ****   * @brief  Initializes the TIM Encoder Interface and initialize the associated handle.
3016:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_tim.c ****   * @note   Switching from Center Aligned counter mode to Edge counter mode (or reverse)
3017:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_tim.c ****   *         requires a timer reset to avoid unexpected direction
3018:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_tim.c ****   *         due to DIR bit readonly in center aligned mode.
3019:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_tim.c ****   *         Ex: call @ref HAL_TIM_Encoder_DeInit() before HAL_TIM_Encoder_Init()
3020:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_tim.c ****   * @note   Encoder mode and External clock mode 2 are not compatible and must not be selected toge
3021:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_tim.c ****   *         Ex: A call for @ref HAL_TIM_Encoder_Init will erase the settings of @ref HAL_TIM_Config
3022:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_tim.c ****   *         using TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ETRMODE2 and vice versa
3023:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_tim.c ****   * @note   When the timer instance is initialized in Encoder mode, timer
3024:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_tim.c ****   *         channels 1 and channel 2 are reserved and cannot be used for other
